definition.value: Terminology has been varied and somewhat confusing, including involuntary emotional expression disorder, emotional lability, emotional dysregulation, pathological laughter and crying, emotional dysregulation, emotional incontinence, and emotionalism. PBA may be encountered in the setting of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis, extrapyramidal and cerebellar disorders (Parkinson disease, multiple system atrophy, progressive supranuclear palsy), multiple sclerosis, traumatic brain injury, Alzheimer disease and other dementias, stroke, and brain tumors.

value.value: Pseudobulbar signs result from injury to an upper motor neuron lesion to the corticobulbar pathways in the pyramidal tract. Patients have difficulty chewing, swallowing and demonstrate slurred speech (often initial presentation) as well as abnormal behavioral symptoms such as inappropriate emotional outbursts of uncontrolled laughter or weeping etc.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: The term wooly hair refers to an abnormal variant of hair that is fine, with tightly coiled curls, and often hypopigmented. Electron microscopy may show flat, oval hair shafts with reduced transversal diameter.

definition.value: Affected individuals may present with peripheral edema, diarrhea with or without bleeding, abdominal pain, and/or weight loss. Protein-losing enteropathy is not a disease but is a manifestation of a number of gastrointestinal diseases and can be related to factors such as lymphatic obstruction, mucosal disease with erosions, ulcerations, or increased mucosal permeability to proteins.

https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0002249 (Melena)  ; abnormality of the digestive system ; abnormality of the cardiovascular system ; abnormality of blood and blood-forming tissues

value.value: Gastrointestinal kanamayla ilişkili siyahımsı, katranlı dışkıların geçişi. Melena kolon bakterileri tarafından parçalanmaya yetecek kadar uzun süre boyunca kolonda kalırsa oluşur. Bir bozunma ürünü, hematin, dışkıyı siyahımsı bir renk ile örter. Bu nedenle, melena genellikle, alt gastrointestinal kanamadan daha uzun süre bağırsakta kaldığı için, üst gastrointestinal sistem kanaması ile oluşur (örneğin, sotmach ülseri veya duodenum ülseri)

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: The passage of blackish, tarry feces associated with gastrointestinal hemorrhage. Melena occurs if the blood remains in the colon long enough for it to be broken down by colonic bacteria. One degradation product, hematin, imbues the stool with a blackish color. Thus, melena generally occurs with bleeding from the upper gastrointestinal tract (e.g., stomach ulcers or duodenal ulcers), since the blood usually remains in the gut for a longer period of time than with lower gastrointestinal bleeding.

Vylučování černých, dehtovitých výkalů spojené s krvácením do zažívacího traktu. K meléně dochází, pokud krev zůstane v tlustém střevě dostatečně dlouho na to, aby ji mohly rozložit bakterie tlustého střeva. Jeden z produktů rozkladu, hematin, dodává stolici černou barvu. Meléna se tedy obvykle vyskytuje při krvácení z horní části trávicího traktu (např. žaludeční vředy nebo vředy dvanáctníku), protože krev obvykle zůstává ve střevě delší dobu než při krvácení z dolní části trávicího traktu.
